WEBVTT

00:06.273 --> 00:07.708
Oh, shut up, Dolly, get on with it.

00:07.741 --> 00:09.109
Don't talk to me like... okay.

00:10.678 --> 00:13.080
Just as I said, don't step on my foot.

00:13.113 --> 00:15.315
- Okay, darling. Okay.
- That's all I want...

00:15.348 --> 00:18.151
Have you seen my black toe?

00:18.185 --> 00:19.065
Well, how did you...

00:19.067 --> 00:21.090
I didn't stand on it on my own, darling.

00:21.121 --> 00:23.490
- One, two, three, four. Good.
- One, two, three, four.

00:23.524 --> 00:26.627
- You're such a good teacher, darling.
- I know I am.

00:28.000 --> 00:34.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:41.074 --> 00:44.077
- And one, and two...
- Three. Now we go sideways.

00:44.111 --> 00:46.479
- Yes, okay.
- And don't forget. And side.

01:01.094 --> 01:02.530
What is going on?

01:03.964 --> 01:05.197
Dorottya.

01:05.232 --> 01:07.400
May I inquire what on earth is going on?

01:07.434 --> 01:09.069
Well, good morning, Ms. Trudeau.

01:09.102 --> 01:11.238
Freddy and Dolly were just
having an early morning dance,

01:11.271 --> 01:13.807
and they weren't dressed warm enough,
you know, so I thought that...

01:13.841 --> 01:16.109
- It is not your place, Dorottya.
- Mrs. Trudeau.

01:16.143 --> 01:18.478
You should have notified
the night nurse.

01:18.512 --> 01:21.048
I'll take over now...
Thank you.

01:21.081 --> 01:24.084
Merciful God, I'm so bored.

01:25.452 --> 01:27.320
Bored, bored.

01:27.354 --> 01:29.122
- Why?
- Must one have a reason?

01:29.156 --> 01:31.525
It depends what you're bored with.

01:31.559 --> 01:34.227
For one thing, you're the queen.
I'm glad you mentioned it.

01:34.261 --> 01:36.229
You've been on a crusade.

01:36.263 --> 01:38.331
You must have seen wonderful things,

01:38.365 --> 01:40.300
things that I've only dreamed of.

01:40.333 --> 01:42.670
And do you dream a lot,
Henry Plantagenet?

01:42.703 --> 01:45.906
Yes, I do. I hold the world in my hands.

01:45.939 --> 01:48.341
Daddy, please, be reasonable.
For once.

01:48.375 --> 01:50.410
That's a big dream.

01:50.443 --> 01:53.146
Yes. Tell me about Jerusalem.

01:53.180 --> 01:55.015
Jerusalem.

01:55.048 --> 01:57.384
Jerusalem was boring and very hot.

01:59.052 --> 02:00.854
Dimitri, Dimitri.

02:00.888 --> 02:03.757
What have I done that I should
be treated so disrespectfully?

02:03.791 --> 02:07.294
- Please stop being such an old ham.
- That it should come to this.

02:07.327 --> 02:08.562
Hmm?

02:08.596 --> 02:10.698
Hiring somebody to care about me.

02:10.731 --> 02:12.866
Caring for you.
It's not the same thing.

02:12.900 --> 02:15.002
We could never hope to pay
anyone to care about you.

02:15.035 --> 02:16.870
Oh!

02:16.904 --> 02:21.474
Thank you, Sophia. Always a kind word
for your dying father.

02:21.509 --> 02:23.176
Just see her for a few minutes.

02:23.210 --> 02:25.879
Talk to her, is that too much to ask?

02:25.913 --> 02:27.848
- Is she a Muslim?
- Oh, don't start that again.

02:27.881 --> 02:30.250
- Of course she's not a Muslim.
- The last one was a Muslim.

02:30.283 --> 02:32.219
- No, she wasn't. She was Russian.
- She had a burka.

02:32.252 --> 02:34.822
She didn't have a burka.
She had a cold.

02:34.855 --> 02:37.124
- I'm still not interested.
- Daddy, please.

02:37.157 --> 02:38.792
Oh! Bugger off!

02:39.693 --> 02:41.962
And let me rest in peace.

02:49.703 --> 02:52.339
You didn't say you were going
straight to the Oscars.

02:57.545 --> 03:00.814
I wish you all the luck in the world.

03:00.848 --> 03:04.451
- You must be Dorothy.
- Yes, Dorottya. Dorottya Horvat.

03:04.484 --> 03:08.288
- I'm Sir Michael Gifford's chauffeur.
- Nice to meet you, hello.

03:08.321 --> 03:09.590
Mmm...

03:40.721 --> 03:42.856
Sorry, what was your name?

03:42.890 --> 03:45.559
Joseph, miss... Joseph McGill.

03:45.593 --> 03:48.529
And how long have you been
working for Sir Gifford, Joseph?

03:49.196 --> 03:50.764
Over 40 years.

03:50.798 --> 03:52.833
My father saw his Lear in Belgrade.

03:52.866 --> 03:55.435
He used to rave about it all the time.

03:55.468 --> 03:57.470
- I was there, you know.
- No way.

03:57.505 --> 03:59.807
- I was his dresser back then.
- Amazing.

03:59.840 --> 04:03.276
He was the life and soul of the company.

04:03.310 --> 04:05.178
He'd be laughing and
joking in the wings,

04:05.212 --> 04:08.916
and then go on stage and play tragedy.

04:08.949 --> 04:10.283
If he had to cry in the part,

04:10.317 --> 04:13.286
I'd be waiting there in the wings
with a glass of champagne,

04:13.320 --> 04:15.222
to dab his eyes.

04:15.255 --> 04:19.959
Piper Heidsieck, 2002.
That's the year at the moment.

04:21.361 --> 04:26.066
Nowadays, I work mostly
for his daughter, Mrs. Morley.

04:26.099 --> 04:28.268
- Doing what?
- Driving.

04:28.301 --> 04:30.437
I do the gardening.
Lovely garden.

04:30.470 --> 04:33.406
- So you don't dress him anymore?
- Good God, no.

04:33.440 --> 04:37.077
He hates that now.
Hates being dependent.

04:37.110 --> 04:40.614
Quite right. I hate it, too.

04:40.648 --> 04:42.082
Well, I'm told he is difficult.

04:42.115 --> 04:44.151
No, no, miss, that's not right.

04:45.452 --> 04:47.454
He's bloody impossible.

05:05.739 --> 05:07.541
Wow.

05:08.742 --> 05:10.644
My God.

05:10.678 --> 05:12.846
- Rather big, isn't it?
- Oh, yes. Let me help you.

05:12.880 --> 05:13.947
No, no. No, no, no.

05:13.981 --> 05:16.449
I tell you, it's a nightmare to keep up.

05:16.483 --> 05:19.052
That's why I work in the garden.

05:19.086 --> 05:22.990
And, um, Mrs. Morley?
What's she like?

05:23.023 --> 05:27.728
She's her father's daughter.
Very strong willed.

05:27.761 --> 05:29.530
She wants him to sell up
and move in with her.

05:29.563 --> 05:33.133
But Sir Michael's lived
the whole of his life here.

05:33.166 --> 05:35.769
The best years, anyway.

05:35.803 --> 05:37.170
Oh, well.

05:40.774 --> 05:43.076
Hello, Miss Horvat.

05:43.110 --> 05:45.546
Dorottya, isn't it?

05:45.579 --> 05:49.182
Unusual name. Though not if
you're Romanian, of course.

05:49.216 --> 05:52.920
Hungarian, actually.
I am 100 percent Hungarian.

05:52.953 --> 05:55.556
- Even if my name is Horvat.
- Yes, yes, of course.

05:55.589 --> 05:58.826
Which in Hungarian means "Croat".
But I am Hungarian.

05:58.859 --> 06:00.594
My mistake entirely.

06:00.628 --> 06:03.330
This is Dr. Alastair Satterthwaite,
my father's doctor.

06:03.363 --> 06:04.632
A pleasure to meet you.

06:04.665 --> 06:07.334
And this is Milly Holcombe,
she manages the house.

06:07.367 --> 06:08.902
Miss Horvat, I'm very sorry,

06:08.936 --> 06:11.672
but it seems like you've come
all this way for no reason.

06:11.705 --> 06:14.808
My father refuses
to have you as his carer.

06:14.842 --> 06:16.610
I am very sorry.

06:16.644 --> 06:18.679
I don't know what you mean.
Sir Gifford hasn't even met me.

06:18.712 --> 06:20.047
You mean, "Sir Michael."

06:20.080 --> 06:22.716
We don't say "Sir Gifford"
in this country.

06:25.619 --> 06:27.187
I'm sorry.

06:27.220 --> 06:29.690
Perhaps if we let Miss Horvat
stay for a few days...

06:29.723 --> 06:31.759
I don't think that's a good idea.

06:31.792 --> 06:32.465
It's a jolly good idea.

06:32.467 --> 06:33.928
He might change his mind.
Just to spite you.

06:33.961 --> 06:37.965
Joseph and I are perfectly capable of
looking after Michael. We really are.

06:37.998 --> 06:40.300
Joseph hates doing it.
He said so himself.

06:40.333 --> 06:42.002
And Sir Michael hates it, too.

06:44.538 --> 06:46.173
You already know, I gather,

06:46.206 --> 06:48.942
that Sir Michael suffers from
a rare type of Parkinson's disease.

06:48.976 --> 06:51.244
- Yes.
- He has his good days, and,

06:51.278 --> 06:53.547
well, less good ones.

06:53.581 --> 06:57.184
For the time being, we can alleviate
the symptoms with medication,

06:57.217 --> 07:01.722
but he soon might need to be
bathed, taken to the lavatory.

07:03.223 --> 07:06.159
Wiped, if needs be.

07:06.193 --> 07:09.396
Are you quite sure you're the kind
of person that could do that?

07:09.429 --> 07:10.764
Definitely, yes.

07:11.799 --> 07:14.768
Unfortunately, I...
I have experience.

07:14.802 --> 07:16.570
Before my father died, near the end,

07:16.604 --> 07:18.171
I saw how much he was suffering

07:18.205 --> 07:21.008
because he couldn't produce...
Stool?

07:22.075 --> 07:23.210
Yes, the word is stool.

07:24.311 --> 07:26.379
So sometimes I took him
into the lavatory,

07:26.413 --> 07:29.016
and I put my finger into his, uh...

07:29.049 --> 07:29.867
Rectum...

07:29.869 --> 07:32.320
Rectum, yes, thank you.
To relieve him.

07:32.352 --> 07:36.123
I didn't like doing it, but he was
my father, and he was in pain.

07:36.156 --> 07:37.958
And that's what it's all about, right?

07:38.859 --> 07:41.028
Helping and relieving.

07:43.196 --> 07:46.399
Okay, well, I suppose
you can stay for a day or two.

07:46.433 --> 07:48.468
Milly, will you take care
of Miss Horvat?

07:48.502 --> 07:50.971
Make sure she's fed and...
Well, you know.

07:52.072 --> 07:53.440
Is that okay with everyone?
Good.

07:55.042 --> 07:58.045
So, what made them
change their minds, miss?

07:58.846 --> 08:01.014
- I did.
- Oh!

08:02.482 --> 08:05.085
Excuse me, where is this one from?

08:05.118 --> 08:08.155
Oh, Lord. BBC.

08:08.188 --> 08:09.657
Some king or other.

08:10.423 --> 08:13.661
Lots of kings. 1978.

08:13.694 --> 08:17.330
- And that one up there?
- Troilus and Cressida.

08:18.165 --> 08:19.232
Very good.

08:34.414 --> 08:35.482
Shit.

08:37.450 --> 08:39.186
A- ha!

08:39.219 --> 08:40.486
Got you, you little bastard.

09:02.309 --> 09:04.477
Yes. Okay, you're
going back in the pond.

09:06.346 --> 09:07.380
Yes.

09:09.116 --> 09:10.117
Shit.

09:19.893 --> 09:21.261
Argh!

09:21.294 --> 09:22.896
Help!

09:22.930 --> 09:24.331
Someone, come on!

09:25.465 --> 09:26.734
Help me!

09:26.767 --> 09:29.302
Hey! Someone fucking help me!

09:29.336 --> 09:30.437
Help me!

09:41.281 --> 09:43.551
When you've quite finished gawking,

09:43.584 --> 09:48.088
would you please be so kind as to get
me out of this suppurating rose bush?

09:48.121 --> 09:50.558
I feel like Buster fucking Keaton
on a bad day.

09:57.464 --> 10:00.100
- Who the fuck are you?
- I am Dorottya.

10:00.133 --> 10:01.602
I didn't ask your sodding name,

10:01.635 --> 10:02.803
I asked who the fuck you are.

10:02.836 --> 10:04.838
What are you doing in my garden?

10:04.872 --> 10:06.540
I'm your new career.

10:07.808 --> 10:09.877
- You're my "new career"?
- Yes.

10:09.910 --> 10:11.745
Now, there's a depressing thought.

10:13.581 --> 10:15.348
Fucking frogs!

10:15.382 --> 10:18.285
I've spent a fortune on this
adventure park for them,

10:18.318 --> 10:20.320
and the little buggers
won't even go near the place.

10:20.353 --> 10:21.922
Why do you think that is?

10:21.955 --> 10:24.658
They just can't appreciate beauty.

10:26.359 --> 10:27.861
What did you say your name was, again?

10:27.895 --> 10:29.997
Dordogne? Torino? Burrito?

10:30.030 --> 10:32.199
Dorottya.

10:32.232 --> 10:35.268
You're a scrawny little thing.
I pulled you up, didn't I?

10:35.302 --> 10:36.904
Not very pretty.
Actually... Well, I think...

10:38.238 --> 10:40.974
You look like a girl
I used to fancy in nursery.

10:41.008 --> 10:42.409
Which you look as
if you're still attending.

10:42.442 --> 10:44.978
And don't say I look like someone.

10:45.012 --> 10:46.747
I'm too famous to look like anyone else.

10:46.780 --> 10:48.415
Other people look like me.

10:48.448 --> 10:49.783
If they're lucky.

10:50.317 --> 10:51.952
Oh! Oh.

10:51.985 --> 10:54.788
I think I need to lie down.
I'm going to be sick.

10:54.822 --> 10:56.690
Oh! No.

10:58.058 --> 10:59.426
Michael.

10:59.459 --> 11:03.430
Michael, you are all right?
What's happening?

11:03.463 --> 11:06.233
Don't fuss, Milly. I'm all right.
Tickety boo, never better.

11:06.266 --> 11:08.335
You are covered in rose petals.

11:08.368 --> 11:10.303
- Oh, yes, yes, rose petals.
- Didn't you know?

11:10.337 --> 11:11.772
This young lady and I just got married.

11:11.805 --> 11:13.741
- Really?
- I'm sorry you haven't been introduced.

11:13.774 --> 11:17.845
This is Lady Dordogne
Dorito Burrito Gifford.

11:17.878 --> 11:20.213
And we're on our way
to consummate the union.

11:20.247 --> 11:23.450
For God's sake.
Oh, Milly, please, don't upset yourself.

11:23.483 --> 11:26.887
Just go back where you came
from and leave me alone.

11:26.920 --> 11:28.488
Michael, this is the girl
you told Sophia...

11:28.522 --> 11:31.659
"Take thy form from off my door!

11:31.692 --> 11:35.128
"You fucking Raven, nevermore."

11:44.505 --> 11:47.240
Silly cow.

11:47.274 --> 11:51.779
Problem is, she adores me,
so I can't be too hard on her.

11:53.313 --> 11:54.982
You did well, Tortilla.

11:55.816 --> 11:57.651
Dorottya.
Whatever.

11:59.052 --> 12:01.689
- Tell me who you are again.
- I am your career.

12:01.722 --> 12:03.356
- Carer.
- "Carer."

12:03.390 --> 12:06.026
- The word is pronounced "carer."
- Carer.

12:10.130 --> 12:12.900
You haven't got a...

12:12.933 --> 12:15.836
Oh, no, I don't smoke. And I don't
think that you should, either.

12:15.869 --> 12:18.071
Who the fuck cares what you think?

12:19.540 --> 12:21.509
I'm a dying man,

12:21.542 --> 12:24.111
and it's traditional to give
a dying man a cigarette.

12:24.144 --> 12:27.180
You'll find some over there.

12:27.214 --> 12:32.252
In the Complete Works,
Shakespeare, page 1613.

12:37.324 --> 12:39.192
Ah! Mmm.

12:51.639 --> 12:55.909
Now, you, too,
quickly pave the way to hell.

13:21.902 --> 13:24.037
- Hello, miss.
- I'm so sorry. Hi.

13:24.071 --> 13:26.907
How are you getting
along with Sir Michael?

13:26.940 --> 13:30.611
I'm not. Milly will hardly
let me near him.

13:30.644 --> 13:32.312
I'll have a word.

13:33.213 --> 13:34.548
Excuse me.

13:35.148 --> 13:36.249
Hello.

13:39.419 --> 13:41.555
A letter came for you.

13:41.589 --> 13:42.856
Turn on your video.

13:46.059 --> 13:48.028
It's from the drama school.

13:48.061 --> 13:49.496
What does it say?

13:52.265 --> 13:54.835
"Dear Miss Dorottya Horvat."

13:54.868 --> 13:58.138
"We are pleased to inform you,
that your application..."

13:58.171 --> 14:00.974
You are in.
You've passed the first test.

14:01.008 --> 14:02.576
- No way.
- Successful.

14:02.610 --> 14:05.478
You have to ring some Ms. Henderson

14:05.513 --> 14:08.348
to confirm your appointment
for the second round.

14:08.381 --> 14:10.383
Don't forget to give them
your new address.

14:10.417 --> 14:12.920
"Care of Sir Michael Gifford,"
they'll love that.

14:12.953 --> 14:13.987
Dorottya!

14:14.655 --> 14:16.323
Dorottya!

14:16.356 --> 14:17.925
- She's over here.
- Where is "here"?

14:17.958 --> 14:19.527
I have to go now. Bye.

14:19.560 --> 14:21.795
Bye, Joseph.
Helping me in the garden.

14:21.829 --> 14:25.633
We don't pay her to help you in
the garden. Tell her to come at once.

14:25.666 --> 14:27.334
- Go away!
- Michael, it's only Milly.

14:27.367 --> 14:29.402
- Leave me alone!
- Michael, please.

14:30.771 --> 14:32.472
- What's wrong?
- I said, fuck off!

14:32.506 --> 14:34.241
I think he had an accident.

14:34.274 --> 14:36.276
- I'm coming in.
- Go away!

14:40.380 --> 14:43.584
- Oh, no.
- Yes, it stinks.

14:43.617 --> 14:47.254
Stinkus, stinka, stinkum.

14:47.287 --> 14:50.558
Did you...
Well, obviously I did.

14:50.591 --> 14:54.628
- A number two?
- Of course it's a fucking number two!

14:54.662 --> 14:56.997
Is this how pee smells in Bulgaria?

14:57.030 --> 14:59.567
Hungary.
Fuck Hungary!

14:59.600 --> 15:01.401
Oh! Just leave me alone!

15:01.434 --> 15:03.270
Of course I'm not
just gonna leave you alone.

15:10.010 --> 15:13.146
"What's in a name?"

15:13.180 --> 15:19.753
"That which we call a rose by any
other name would smell as sweet."

15:23.290 --> 15:27.761
"Speak the speech, I pray you,
as I pronounced it to you,

15:27.795 --> 15:30.030
trippingly on the tongue,

15:30.063 --> 15:34.301
but if you mouth it,
as many of your players do,

15:34.334 --> 15:38.405
I had as lief the town-crier
spoke my lines."

15:38.438 --> 15:43.343
"Be not too tame neither, but let
your own discretion be your tutor."

15:43.376 --> 15:45.913
How the fuck do you do that?

15:45.946 --> 15:48.516
When you can't even
speak proper English.

15:50.150 --> 15:52.252
- I've been on the stage.
- Oh.

15:54.387 --> 15:56.757
Now, just relax.

15:59.159 --> 16:01.394
Oh, God.

16:01.428 --> 16:02.604
No, I'm afraid, I think...

16:02.606 --> 16:04.866
Probably, this is the
best thing to do then.

16:04.898 --> 16:06.967
Okay.
No, I'll tell her. I'll tell her.

16:07.000 --> 16:10.103
All right. Thank you very much. Bye-bye.

16:13.006 --> 16:14.708
So...

16:14.742 --> 16:17.511
The job is yours if you want it.

16:17.545 --> 16:19.279
- Thank you.
- I mean it.

16:19.312 --> 16:21.849
No, don't thank me.
It was Sophia's decision.

16:29.389 --> 16:31.458
I hope you'll last.

16:31.491 --> 16:32.960
I'll be okay.

16:38.265 --> 16:42.035
So, after what's happened we'll have
to bring Michael's bed downstairs

16:42.069 --> 16:44.204
and put it in the dining room.

16:44.237 --> 16:47.575
And convert the scullery
into a bathroom.

16:47.608 --> 16:49.643
Sir Michael's going to sleep
in the dining room?

16:51.845 --> 16:53.013
Yep.

16:56.049 --> 16:58.752
And you'll be next door.
It won't be as nice as it was upstairs,

16:58.786 --> 17:02.122
but you'll have to stay
close to him day and night.

17:13.300 --> 17:16.503
I'll arrange your pillows.
You should sleep.

17:16.537 --> 17:19.439
Oh! So now you're gonna
tell me when to sleep?

17:19.472 --> 17:23.511
I'm sorry I got that wrong.
I should sleep.

17:23.544 --> 17:26.279
You were hired to give
a 24 hour service.

17:26.313 --> 17:29.617
Exactly.
And the 25th hour is just starting.

17:36.256 --> 17:37.290
Sweet dreams.

17:51.972 --> 17:53.874
"To be or not to be."

17:55.108 --> 17:56.109
No, no.

17:57.177 --> 17:59.513
To be or not to be.

18:00.581 --> 18:01.782
That is...

18:02.683 --> 18:03.984
Dorottya!

18:04.017 --> 18:05.385
That is the question.

18:05.418 --> 18:06.754
Dorottya!

18:10.457 --> 18:13.193
Do you know this?
This is why you called?

18:13.226 --> 18:16.764
- Do you know it or not?
- Of course I do.

18:16.797 --> 18:17.972
To Be or Not to Be.

18:17.974 --> 18:21.002
Do you know, it was
all made by Hungarians.

18:21.034 --> 18:24.705
Hungarian producer, Hungarian cameraman,
Hungarian set designer.

18:24.738 --> 18:26.707
Even the man who wrote
the script was a Hungarian.

18:26.740 --> 18:28.809
Hungarian my arse.
He was Polish.

18:28.842 --> 18:30.778
Why do you always have to argue?

18:30.811 --> 18:32.224
His name is Melchior Lengyel.

18:32.226 --> 18:34.516
Which means Polish,
but he was Hungarian.

