26:35.963 --> 26:37.898
"I do not have the skill."

26:39.633 --> 26:40.801
No.

26:41.569 --> 26:43.403
You have not the skill.

26:45.238 --> 26:48.241
You have absolutely no chance
of making it on the stage here.

26:53.747 --> 26:56.449
- I can learn.
- You certainly need to.

26:56.483 --> 26:58.385
- Then teach me.
- Out of the question.

26:58.418 --> 27:01.121
- Why?
- You have to look up to your teacher.

27:01.154 --> 27:02.723
But I do look up to you.

27:02.756 --> 27:05.626
Of course. From below.
When you're washing my arse.

27:21.274 --> 27:23.476
- Hello, Joseph.
- Hey.

27:23.511 --> 27:25.513
- Will you take her around?
- You bet.

27:27.748 --> 27:29.517
Where's Milly?

27:29.550 --> 27:32.252
She's taking Dorottya
to the train station.

27:32.285 --> 27:34.688
She's been telling me
how well you get on with her.

27:34.722 --> 27:36.957
- I'm so pleased.
- With whom?

27:38.091 --> 27:40.060
Miss Horvat.

27:40.093 --> 27:43.163
Alastair also says she's
doing a first-class job.

27:43.196 --> 27:46.266
I haven't the foggiest idea
who you're talking about.

27:46.299 --> 27:49.369
Of course you do.
Joseph picked her out for you.

27:49.402 --> 27:53.406
Which immediately made her far more
suitable than the ones I found.

27:53.440 --> 27:57.978
Mmm... "Did I deserve
no more than a fool's head?

27:58.011 --> 27:59.379
"Is that my prize?"

28:03.817 --> 28:07.588
Funny you should mention prizes.
I got a call this morning.

28:07.621 --> 28:10.323
